<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Brisbane's quiet riverside prestige market.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Chelmer sits roughly eight kilometres south-west of the CBD, where the Brisbane River curves around the suburb's northern boundary. It is one of Brisbane's genuinely low-turnover markets: buyers who move into Chelmer tend to stay, which means stock is rarely plentiful and the homes that do come to market attract serious, experienced buyers. The suburb's identity is built on large heritage Queenslanders on generous blocks, a quiet residential character, and river proximity without the price ceiling that comes with Hamilton or Hawthorne.
    </p>
