<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Selling in Chelmer requires a different approach to most inner-Brisbane markets. The buyer pool is smaller, but the buyers are typically well-funded and they know what they want. Reaching them means understanding where they come from: established families relocating from Indooroopilly or Toowong, downsizers who have sold a larger property and want to stay in the river corridor, and prestige buyers from other cities researching Brisbane's inner south-west specifically. A campaign that speaks to that profile, and that understands the Chelmer premium relative to Graceville and Sherwood, is what drives a strong result here.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The streets closest to the river consistently command the highest prices per square metre in Chelmer, with riverfront and river-view homes operating in a category of their own. Heritage character integrity is also a meaningful premium driver: original Queenslanders with retained VJ walls, timber floors, wide verandahs and high ceilings attract buyers who have been searching specifically for that typology and will not substitute a contemporary build. Block size and north-facing aspect are secondary but material factors, particularly for buyers considering future renovation or extension.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229;">
