      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Chelmer?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Chelmer is one of Brisbane's inner south-west prestige markets. Values are driven by river proximity, block size, heritage character integrity and the rarity of stock. Properties on the riverfront or with direct river access consistently command a significant premium over the suburb's internal streets.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Chelmer?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Chelmer's low-turnover market means well-presented homes at accurate prices typically sell in 30 to 50 days. The buyer pool is smaller than comparable inner-east suburbs, but the buyers who are active in Chelmer are serious and usually equity-rich, which translates to decisive action when the right property appears.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What makes Chelmer different from neighbouring suburbs?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">The Brisbane River wraps around Chelmer's northern boundary, and the suburb retains a concentration of large heritage Queenslanders on generous blocks that is increasingly rare so close to the CBD. It is quieter and lower-turnover than Graceville or Sherwood, and the buyer who targets Chelmer specifically is usually seeking that combination of river access, character architecture and an established neighbourhood.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Chelmer a good suburb to sell in?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Chelmer is a strong seller's market for correctly prepared and priced properties. Low stock means limited competing supply, which works in a seller's favour. The key is reaching the right buyer pool, which tends to stretch from established families upsizing within the inner south-west to prestige buyers looking for river proximity without the price premium of Hamilton or Hawthorne.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

